.TH "of_pm_clk_add_clk" 9 "of_pm_clk_add_clk" "May 2021" "Kernel Hacker's Manual" LINUX
.SH NAME
of_pm_clk_add_clk \- Start using a device clock for power management.
.SH SYNOPSIS
.B "int" of_pm_clk_add_clk
.BI "(struct device *dev "  ","
.BI "const char *name "  ");"
.SH ARGUMENTS
.IP "dev" 12
Device whose clock is going to be used for power management.
.IP "name" 12
Name of clock that is going to be used for power management.
.SH "DESCRIPTION"
Add the clock described in the 'clocks' device-tree node that matches
with the 'name' provided, to the list of clocks used for the power
management of \fIdev\fP. On success, returns 0. Returns a negative error
code if the clock is not found or cannot be added.
